	Summary
	Prospectus-January 31, 2016



	Before you
	invest in the SPDR

	®

	S&P

	®

	International
	Small Cap ETF (the “Fund”), you may want to review the Fund's prospectus and statement of additional information, which contain more information about the Fund and the risks of investing in the Fund. The Fund's prospectus and statement
	of additional information dated January 31, 2016, are incorporated by reference into this summary prospectus. You can find the Fund's prospectus and statement of additional information, as well as other information about the Fund, online at

	https://www.spdrs.com/product/fund.seam?ticker=GWX.



	You may also obtain this information at no charge by
	calling 1-866-787-2257 or by sending an e-mail request to Fund_inquiry@ssga.com.





	Investment
	Objective




	The
	SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF (the “Fund”) seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of an index based upon the developed world (ex-US) small cap
	equity markets.







	Fees and
	Expenses of the Fund


	The table below describes
	the fees and expenses that you may pay if you buy and hold shares of the Fund (“Fund Shares”). This table and the Example below reflect the expenses of the Fund and do not reflect brokerage commissions you may pay on purchases and sales
	of Fund Shares.


