	Purchase and Sale Information


	The Fund will issue (or redeem) Fund Shares to
	certain institutional investors (typically market makers or other broker-dealers) only in large blocks of 100,000 Fund Shares known as “Creation Units.” Creation Unit transactions are typically conducted in exchange for the deposit or
	delivery of a designated portfolio of in-kind securities and/or cash constituting a substantial replication, or a representation, of the securities included in the Fund's benchmark Index.


	Individual Fund Shares may only be purchased and
	sold on the NYSE Arca, Inc., other national securities exchanges, electronic crossing networks and other alternative trading systems through your broker-dealer at market prices. Because Fund Shares trade at market prices rather than at net asset
	value (“NAV”), Fund Shares may trade at a price greater than NAV (premium) or less than NAV (discount).




