SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 12:51 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF



Snapshot People




Company Overview
SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by State Street Global Advisors, Inc. The fund is managed by SSGA Funds Management, Inc. It invests in public equity markets across the globe, excluding the United States. The fund seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in stocks of large cap and mid cap companies. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the MSCI All Country World Index ex USA Index, by using representative sampling technique. It was formerly known as streetTRACKS Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF. SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF was formed on ...
SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by State Street Global Advisors, Inc. The fund is managed by SSGA Funds Management, Inc. It invests in public equity markets across the globe, excluding the United States. The fund seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in stocks of large cap and mid cap companies. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the MSCI All Country World Index ex USA Index, by using representative sampling technique. It was formerly known as streetTRACKS Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF. SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR MSCI ACWI ex-US ETF was formed on January 10, 2007 and is domiciled in the United States.
