SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 12:51 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF



Snapshot People




Company Overview
SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by State Street Global Advisors, Inc. The fund is managed by SSGA Funds Management, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets of developed countries across the globe, excluding the United States. The fund seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in stocks of small cap companies with a market capitalization between $100 million and $2 billion. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the S&P Developed Ex-U.S. Under USD2 Billion Index, by using representative sampling technique. It was formerly known as streetTRACKS Index Shares Fu...
SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by State Street Global Advisors, Inc. The fund is managed by SSGA Funds Management, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets of developed countries across the globe, excluding the United States. The fund seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in stocks of small cap companies with a market capitalization between $100 million and $2 billion. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the S&P Developed Ex-U.S. Under USD2 Billion Index, by using representative sampling technique. It was formerly known as streetTRACKS Index Shares Funds - SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF. SPDR Index Shares Funds - SPDR S&P International Small Cap ETF was formed on April 20, 2007 and is domiciled in the United States.
